chapter AFP

session ByzantineCD (AFP) = FLP +
  description \<open>
    Mechanisation in Isabelle/HOL of the impossibility results of
    Misra and Kshemkalyani, "Byzantine-tolerant detection of
    causality: There is no holy grail" (Parallel Computing 124,
    2025).  Builds on the AFP entry FLP for the underlying
    asynchronous-system framework and the FLP impossibility
    theorem (invoked, not re-proven).  Mechanises Theorems 1, 2
    (Section 4.1: false negatives unavoidable; FN-or-FP unavoidable
    for internal events) and Theorems 3, 4, 5 (Section 4.2: CD
    unsolvable in unicast / broadcast / multicast in the presence
    of one or more Byzantine processes).
  \<close>
  options [timeout = 600]
  theories
    ByzantineSystem
    Events
    CD
    BlackBox
    Reductions
    Theorems_1_2
    BlackBox_Unsolvable
    FLP_Consensus
    Impossibility
    Foundation_Vacuity
    CD_vs_Consensus
    BHB
    CD_B_Algorithm
    Delivery
  document_files
    "root.tex"
    "root.bib"
